Privacy Policy
Last Updated: November 25, 2024
This Privacy Policy describes our policies and procedures for collecting, using, and disclosing your information
        when you use the Services, and tells you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.
We use your personal data to provide and improve services. By using the Services, you agree to the collection and
        use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
1. Explanation and Definition
1.1 Explanation
Capitalized words have the meanings defined by the following conditions. The following definitions shall have the
        same meaning whether appearing in the singular or the plural.
1.2 Definitions
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:
Affiliate Operator:
An entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control
            with a party, where "control" means an entity that owns 50% or more of the shares, equity, or other rights
            to vote for directors or other governing bodies ownership of securities.
Application:
An operator-provided software program that you download on any electronic
            device named this app.
Operator:
Refers to "us," "we," or "our," meaning this app.
Country:
Refers to China.
Device:
Any device that can access the Services, such as a computer, cell phone, or digital
            tablet.
Personal Data:
Any information relating to an identified or identifiable individual.
Service:
Refers to the Application.
Service Provider:
Any natural or legal person who processes data on behalf of the Operator.
            Refers to third-party operators or individuals employed by the Operator to facilitate the Service, provide
            the Service on behalf of the Operator, perform services related to the Service, or assist the Operator in
            analyzing the use of the Service.
Usage Data:
Data that is collected automatically, whether generated through use of the
            Service or from the Service infrastructure itself (for example, the duration of page visits).
You:
The individual accessing or using the Services, or the operator or other legal entity
            (as applicable) accessing or using the Services on behalf of that individual.
2. Collection and Use of Your Personal Data
2.1 Types of Data Collected
2.1.1 Personal Data
When using our Services, we may ask you to provide certain personally identifiable information that can be used
        to contact or identify you. Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to:
Email address
Location
Usage data
2.1.2 Usage Data
Usage data is automatically collected when using the Services.
Usage data may include information such as your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address, browser type, browser
        version, the pages of our Services that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those
        pages, unique device identifiers, and other diagnostic data.
When you access the Services through a mobile device, we may automatically collect certain information, including
        but not limited to:
The type of mobile device you use
Your mobile device's unique ID
Your mobile device's IP address
Your mobile operating system
The type of mobile Internet browser you use
Unique device identifiers
Other diagnostic data
We may also collect information sent by your browser when you visit our Services or access the Services through a
        mobile device.
2.2 Use of Your Personal Data
The Operator may use your personal data for the following purposes:
To provide and maintain our Services:
Including monitoring the usage of our Services to
            ensure optimal performance and functionality.
Manage your account:
To manage your registration as a user of the Services. The personal
            data you provide may allow you to access different features of the Services available to registered users.
For the performance of a contract:
To fulfill, comply with, and manage any purchase
            contract for products, items, or services you have purchased, or any other contract you have with us through
            the Services.
To contact you:
To communicate with you via email, phone calls, text messages, or other
            equivalent forms of electronic communication, such as push notifications from mobile applications, regarding
            updates, features, products, or contractual services (including security updates) as necessary or
            reasonable.
To provide you with news and offers:
To send you news, special offers, and general
            information about other goods, services, and events that are similar to those you have already purchased or
            inquired about, unless you have opted out of receiving such information.
Manage your requests:
To respond to and manage your requests submitted to us.
For business transfers:
To evaluate or conduct a merger, divestiture, reorganization,
            dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some or all of our assets, whether as a going concern or as part
            of bankruptcy, liquidation, or similar proceedings, in which personal data held by us about our Service
            users is among the assets transferred.
For other purposes:
We may use your information for other purposes, such as data analysis,
            identifying usage trends, determining the effectiveness of our promotional campaigns, and evaluating and
            improving our Services, products, marketing, and your overall experience.
2.3 Sharing Your Personal Data
We may share your personal data in the following situations:
With service providers:
We may share your personal data with service providers to monitor
            and analyze the use of our Services or to contact you.
For business transfers:
We may share or transfer your personal data in connection with, or
            during negotiations of, any merger, sale of Operator assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion
            of our business by another Operator.
With affiliated operators:
We may share your information with our affiliated operators. In
            such cases, we will require those affiliated operators to comply with this Privacy Policy. Affiliated
            operators include our parent company, subsidiaries, joint venture partners, or other companies that we
            control or are under common control with us.
With business partners:
We may share your information with our business partners to offer
            you certain products, services, or promotions.
With other users:
When you share personal information or otherwise interact with other
            users in public areas, such information may be viewed by all users and may be publicly distributed outside
            the Services.
With your consent:
We may disclose your personal data for any other purpose with your
            explicit consent.
For AI-powered services:
To provide AI-powered features such as text translation, polish,
            reply, sentiment analysis, and other related functionalities.
To optimize and improve:
To enhance the performance and user experience of AI features and
            other Services.
To ensure security and compliance:
To prevent misuse of the Services and ensure compliance
            with applicable laws and regulations.
2.4 Retention of Your Personal Data
The Operator will retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in
        this Privacy Policy. We will retain and use your personal data to the extent required to comply with legal
        obligations (e.g., retaining your data to comply with applicable laws), resolve disputes, and enforce our legal
        agreements and policies.
Usage data will also be retained for internal analysis purposes. Usage data is generally retained for a shorter
        period unless it is used to strengthen security, improve the functionality of our Services, or if we are legally
        required to retain the data for a longer period.
2.5 Transferring Your Personal Data
Your information, including personal data, may be processed at the Operator's operating offices and in any other
        locations where the parties involved in the processing are located. This means your information may be
        transferred to—and stored on—computers located outside your state, province, country, or other governmental
        jurisdiction where data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.
By agreeing to this Privacy Policy and submitting your information, you consent to this transfer.
The Operator will take all reasonable steps to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with
        this Privacy Policy. We will not transfer your personal data to any organization or country unless adequate
        safeguards are in place, including measures to ensure the security of your data and other personal information.
2.6 Disclosure of Your Personal Data
2.6.1 Commercial Transactions
If the Operator is involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your personal data may be transferred as
        part of that transaction. We will provide notice before your personal data is transferred and becomes subject to
        a different privacy policy.
2.6.2 Legal Compliance
In certain circumstances, the Operator may be required to disclose your personal data to comply with legal
        obligations or in response to valid requests from public authorities, such as courts or government agencies.
2.6.3 Other Legal Requirements
The Operator may disclose your personal data in good faith, believing that such action is necessary to:
Comply with a legal obligation
Protect and defend the rights or property of the Operator
Prevent or investigate possible misconduct related to the Services
Protect the personal safety of users of the Services or the public
Prevent legal liability
2.7 Security of Your Personal Data
The security of your personal data is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the
        Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we endeavour to use commercially acceptable means
        to protect your personal data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
3. Limitations and Risks of AI Features
3.1 Privacy Risks of Generated Content
AI features may generate results based on the content you provide. To protect your privacy, please avoid
        inputting sensitive personal information, confidential data, or any content that could compromise your security.
3.2 User Responsibility
You are solely responsible for the content generated using AI features and any actions related to its sharing,
        distribution, or use. Please ensure that the content complies with applicable laws and does not infringe on the
        rights of others.
4. Children's Privacy
Our Services are not intended for individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally
        identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your
        child has provided us with personal data, please contact us immediately. If we become aware that we have
        collected personal data from anyone under the age of 13 without verified parental consent, we will take prompt
        steps to delete such information from our servers.
If consent is required as a legal basis for processing personal data in your jurisdiction, and your country
        mandates parental consent, we may request parental consent before collecting or using such information.
5. Links to Other Websites
Our Services may contain links to third-party websites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party
        link, you will be redirected to that third party's website. We strongly encourage you to review the privacy
        policy of every website you visit.
We have no control over, and assume no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any
        third-party websites or services.
6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated by posting the updated
        Privacy Policy on this page.
We will notify you of significant changes via email and/or a prominent notice on our Services before the changes
        take effect. The "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy will also be revised accordingly.
We encourage you to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed about how we are protecting your
        information. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective immediately upon being posted on this page.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you may contact us at:
aiwhizz_feedback@outlook.com
Attachment 1 "This application Permission Application and Usage Description"
1. General Information
To ensure the safe and stable operation of this app, we may apply for or use relevant operating system
            permissions based on actual business scenarios.
To protect your right to know, we provide a detailed list of operating system permissions that the app may
            request or use. You can manage these permissions according to your preferences and needs.
As the app is upgraded, the types and purposes of requested permissions may change based on new features. We
            will update this list promptly to ensure you are informed of any changes.
Please note that for business functionality and security, we may use third-party SDKs based on actual
            business scenarios. These third parties may also request or use relevant operating system permissions.
When using third-party H5 interfaces, applets, or plugins, these third parties may request or use relevant
            operating system permissions based on their functional requirements.
2. List of iOS Operating System App Permissions
1. Push Notifications
Permission Function Description:
Push message notifications
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To notify you about updates or important information
            regarding the app.
Consequences of Refusal:
You will not receive push notifications.
2. Network Extensions
Permission Function Description:
Network access permissions
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To send and receive network data, access third-party links,
            and handle other network requests.
Consequences of Refusal:
The app will not be able to access the internet or perform
            network-related functions.
3. Tracking
Permission Function Description:
Cross-program user tracking
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To obtain your device identifier for data analytics, measure
            and analyze service performance, ensure service security, and improve your user experience.
Consequences of Refusal:
The app will not be able to fully analyze service performance or
            optimize your user experience.
4. Camera
Permission Function Description:
Access to the camera
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To allow you to take photos directly within the app.
Consequences of Refusal:
You will not be able to take photos using the app.
5. Photo Library
Permission Function Description:
Access to your photo library
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To allow you to select and send photos from your album.
Consequences of Refusal:
You will not be able to send photos from your album.
6. Microphone
Permission Function Description:
Access to the microphone
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To allow you to record and send voice messages.
Consequences of Refusal:
You will not be able to record audio using the app.
7. Speech Recognition
Permission Function Description:
Speech-to-text functionality
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To convert your speech into text for display within the app.
Consequences of Refusal:
Speech-to-text functionality will not be available.
8. Clipboard
Permission Function Description:
Access to the clipboard
Usage Scenarios and Purposes:
To quickly paste content using the smart keyboard.
Consequences of Refusal:
You will not be able to paste content from the clipboard quickly.
Attachment 2: This Application Accesses the Third-Party SDK Directory
To ensure the proper functioning of this app and maintain its safe and stable operation, we may integrate
        software development kits (SDKs) provided by third parties. These SDKs are used to achieve specific purposes
        based on actual business needs.
We conduct strict security monitoring of the SDKs used by our partners to ensure data security and protect your
        personal information.
The third-party SDKs we currently use are listed below. Please note that third-party SDKs may modify their data
        processing practices due to version upgrades, policy changes, or other reasons. For the most accurate and
        up-to-date information, please refer to the official privacy policies provided by the respective SDK providers.
1. Umeng SDK
Purpose of Use:
To provide statistical analysis services and basic anti-cheating
            capabilities.
Data Collected:
Device MAC address, unique device identifier (IMEI/OPENUDID/GUID),
            advertising identifier, SIM card IMSI information, network status, WiFi status, WiFi MAC address.
Device Permissions Invoked:
Access network status, access WiFi status, allow applications
            to connect to the network.
Privacy Policy:
https://www.umeng.com/policy
2. AdMob SDK
Purpose of Use:
To deliver advertising information to users and prevent fraudulent
            activities.
Data Collected:
Unique identifier, device type and settings, operating system, mobile
            network information (including carrier name), app version numbers, IP addresses, crash reports.
Device Permissions Invoked:
Access network status, access WiFi status.
Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.cn/privacy
